cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the application of information-theoretic concepts to feedforward neural networks, specifically in the context of bounded rational decision-making. This makes it likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of regularization techniques, which is a common topic in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
